  "text": "Since the presence of a correctly complexed iron ligand is critical for EctD-mediated enzyme catalysis [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] , we determined the iron-content of each of these recombinant proteins and found between 0.87 and 0.96 mole iron per mol of EctD protein. Hence, these recombinant EctD proteins should all be functional. An initial assessment of their enzymatic activities under the same assay conditions as used previously for the ectoine hydroxylases from V. salexigens and S. coelicolor [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] demonstrated that this was indeed the case.",
